				<td colspan="2"><span>No, there will be no transfer of characters.  It really IS a totally different game, and there is simply no way that something like that could work.
<br />

<br />
xp progress is pretty darned quick at early levels, then slows considerably.  Now that I know all the newbie island quests and stuff, I can level any toon from 1 - 7 or so, and complete the citizenship quest on the first night of play (4 hours, maybe?)  
<br />

<br />
My first go round, I got to level four on newbie island, went to town without doing all the IoR (island of refuge) quests on the first night.  I did citizenship quest the next night and dinged about 8.  I was 10 and completing my Bard class quest on my third for fourth night.
<br />

<br />
Now I am in my 20s (lvl 22 Troubador, 23 Carpenter) after a month or so.  I did spend a lot of time tradeskilling though as well.  
<br />

<br />
Now that I know the tradeskill system, I could level an Artisan up REAL fast, especially if I had some money backing me, hehe.  The TS system is going to get a serious overhaul on Wednesday's patch though, so we shall see what happens next.  They have responded though to the general feeling among players that while TS are less mindless than eq1 TS, they are still quite a grind, and some processes will be sped up with things like batch combines for subcombines etc.
<br />

<br />
I have yet to feel the least bit stagnated in the first half of the game.  I can't speak to the later game, but have actually read posts saying that levelling through 30s and 40s was actually TOO easy/fast.</span></td>
